00:04:28.328 --> 00:04:34.706
Now tell me , I want to do startup , and I am a viewer of Love Babbar's channel 

00:04:34.906 --> 00:04:39.443
And i am sitting beside the cofounder sir, tell me the three points 

00:04:39.643 --> 00:04:47.579
There is any viewer that wants to do startup , 3 mistakes or learning that you can give to him/her

00:04:47.779 --> 00:04:51.358
That keep these 3 things in mind , you can save a lot of time 

00:04:51.558 --> 00:04:56.050
1st way is that try by yourself, do mistakes, and then rectify them

00:04:56.250 --> 00:05:00.144
But if I tell you these 3 things then you can save a lot of time 

00:05:00.344 --> 00:05:01.297
As a cofounder 

00:05:01.497 --> 00:05:05.102
Mistakes happens in startups , we can't avoid them like that

00:05:05.302 --> 00:05:12.518
But I will tell you the reasons because of  which startups fails most of the time 

00:05:12.718 --> 00:05:18.804
1. You are not solving the problem for long enough 

00:05:19.004 --> 00:05:22.906
Which is, many people start company by the thing that lets do it for 6 months 

00:05:23.106 --> 00:05:25.384
1 year 

00:05:25.584 --> 00:05:27.787
Company can't be created in 6 months or 1 year

00:05:27.987 --> 00:05:29.260
You have to give time 

00:05:29.460 --> 00:05:34.073
My advise is if you are starting any company 

00:05:34.273 --> 00:05:37.916
Then make sure that you have enough money for yourself 

00:05:38.116 --> 00:05:40.834
If you are not earning for next 4-5 years 

00:05:41.034 --> 00:05:43.492
Then also you can survive 

00:05:43.692 --> 00:05:48.150
and then give yourself 4 to 5 years 

00:05:48.350 --> 00:05:49.967
Then something can happen 

00:05:50.167 --> 00:06:00.518
2. people are not focused , easily gets distracted and want to do many things at a time 

00:06:00.718 --> 00:06:04.334
At present blockchain is famous , so people want to do it

00:06:04.534 --> 00:06:07.804
Crypto , 

00:06:08.004 --> 00:06:13.239
What happens , when you do many things at a time , then you can't do anything properly 

00:06:13.439 --> 00:06:17.468
That is the 2nd primary reason , why startups fail, they do too many things

00:06:17.668 --> 00:06:21.596
Instead of focusing on one thing very very deep

00:06:21.796 --> 00:06:27.060
For example , the most common mistakes early product managers make is 

00:06:27.260 --> 00:06:32.558
That they start focusing on the no of features that they are launching 

00:06:32.758 --> 00:06:35.472
My site is good because there are 15 features 

00:06:35.672 --> 00:06:38.544
His/her side is bad because it has only 10 features 

00:06:38.744 --> 00:06:41.593
But the products that are good , like what's app 

00:06:41.793 --> 00:06:44.733
Simplest messaging app , there is no feature

00:06:44.933 --> 00:06:51.940
Hike used to have too many features , but What's app is successful , because simply focused 

00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:54.526
Focus is important

00:06:54.726 --> 00:06:57.164
I am sure you have also some examples

00:06:57.364 --> 00:06:58.986
I have little  different experience 

00:06:59.186 --> 00:07:01.321
It is not related to coding , my experience is that 

00:07:01.521 --> 00:07:02.752
I went to watch Milkha Singh

00:07:02.952 --> 00:07:07.096
After coming home , I was thinking of doing running , become a runner , will go to Olympic , and bring the gold medal 

00:07:07.296 --> 00:07:11.857
Then I watched Dangal, then decided to become a wrestler

00:07:11.858 --> 00:07:16.943
Then watched Dhoni's movie , then decided to play cricket 

00:07:16.944 --> 00:07:21.485
Things are going on , and you are constantly think to do things based on them 

00:07:21.685 --> 00:07:23.328
4-5 things get accumulated 

00:07:23.528 --> 00:07:29.634
When you will see back 6 moths then you will see that you did nothing in those months 

00:07:29.834 --> 00:07:33.208
I think clarity is very important

00:07:33.408 --> 00:07:38.209
It doesn't mean that what will you do in next 5 years or 10 years 

00:07:38.409 --> 00:07:44.355
For me it is that what I will do in next 6 months 

00:07:44.555 --> 00:07:48.777
If you ask me my plan for next 6 months then I can confidently tell you

00:07:48.977 --> 00:07:52.336
If you ask about 5 years , I have no plan for it now 

00:07:52.536 --> 00:07:54.904
I don't know where world will reach in 5 years 

00:07:55.104 --> 00:07:56.705
Any new tech can  come 

00:07:56.905 --> 00:08:03.925
I have the clarity for 6 moths , and I am confident that I can do it

00:08:04.125 --> 00:08:06.264
Your 1st point is important 

00:08:06.464 --> 00:08:09.142
When I talk to people who are working in  company 

00:08:09.342 --> 00:08:15.698
They are leaving , and there window  is  same of 6moths or 1 year 

00:08:15.898 --> 00:08:20.524
If it works in this window , then I will continue , or i will come back 

00:08:20.724 --> 00:08:27.055
Majority have this window only , if it works in 6 months , or 1 year

00:08:27.255 --> 00:08:29.465
which not happens 

00:08:29.665 --> 00:08:38.985
Final reason why companies do succeed is they are playing in very very small market 

00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:41.951
Sharktank terminology that market size is small 

00:08:42.151 --> 00:08:48.950
If my product is only for 100 people in the world 

00:08:49.150 --> 00:08:57.770
No matter how good is the product , there is a cap to maximum amount of money I can earn 

00:08:57.970 --> 00:09:00.303
And hence the kind of business I can build 

00:09:00.503 --> 00:09:07.349
Vs if market is very big , there are many potential customers 

00:09:07.549 --> 00:09:12.033
If I do mistakes then also my company will get bigger 

00:09:12.233 --> 00:09:15.780
So always play in big markets 

00:09:15.980 --> 00:09:22.369
So this was for your startup viewers , that a cofounder is sharing his learnings 

00:09:22.569 --> 00:09:25.362
From here you got the clarity, that you have to work on these 3 things 

00:09:25.562 --> 00:09:28.196
Don't enter with 6 months or 1 year window

00:09:28.396 --> 00:09:31.562
You should have a safe amount of capital , so that you can sustain 4-5 years 

00:09:31.762 --> 00:09:34.069
It should not happen that you end up in 2 moths 

00:09:34.269 --> 00:09:37.158
So you have to work on these things , then you have to move ahead

00:09:37.358 --> 00:09:40.591
Lets move to next question , which is very important

00:09:40.791 --> 00:09:45.216
I am uploading content since 2.5 -3 years 

00:09:45.416 --> 00:09:48.797
I have observed one thing in coding space/college space 

00:09:48.997 --> 00:09:52.084
That there is a tier mentality , that my college is tier 1

00:09:52.284 --> 00:09:54.861
tier 2, tier 3 

00:09:55.061 --> 00:09:59.173
I can't understand why it is there 

00:09:59.373 --> 00:10:04.233
I had a conversation with a student one year ago  who was from tier 3 college

00:10:04.433 --> 00:10:11.902
He used to think that the people in IIT get placed without any effort 

00:10:12.102 --> 00:10:17.465
Because they are in IITs, companies come and pick everyone 

00:10:17.665 --> 00:10:23.217
There is a line that companies are served to them in plates 

00:10:23.417 --> 00:10:26.615
Actually this is not the case , there also students have to put efforts 

00:10:26.815 --> 00:10:31.809
I am from IIIT Hyderabad 

00:10:32.009 --> 00:10:35.032
It was a tension period during placements 

00:10:35.232 --> 00:10:40.390
I have seen people crying , because companies came but nothing happened

00:10:40.590 --> 00:10:43.413
Left people are nervous 

00:10:43.613 --> 00:10:46.386
So you have to do hard work everywhere 

00:10:46.586 --> 00:10:52.303
But if you take a step back and see why this colleges are classified as tier 1, 2,3 

00:10:52.503 --> 00:10:56.497
By one JEE exam ones capability is not defined 

00:10:56.697 --> 00:11:00.922
But then also why it happens , if I take IIT Bombay

00:11:01.122 --> 00:11:06.633
I don't want to offend anyone , why IIT Bombay is IIT Bombay?

00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:12.075
It is not because there are good professors 

00:11:12.275 --> 00:11:19.075
There is nothing like that teach very well 

00:11:19.275 --> 00:11:23.181
Curriculum is also not that excellent 

00:11:23.381 --> 00:11:27.351
In 1st year they  make us do carpentry

00:11:27.551 --> 00:11:30.973
We have also done welding 

00:11:31.173 --> 00:11:33.838
Now I am doing coding, why are you teaching me welding

00:11:34.038 --> 00:11:35.813
I didn't got it till now

00:11:36.013 --> 00:11:40.136
Curriculum is also not that good but the thing which is very solid

00:11:40.336 --> 00:11:45.147
Is the community, year after year 

00:11:45.347 --> 00:11:50.896
How to learn together and how to learn from the seniors , there are the traditions 

00:11:51.096 --> 00:11:53.443
And everyone is motivated 

00:11:53.643 --> 00:11:59.845
If one is not doing then he/she will feel bad , everyone around me is doing then why I am not doing

00:12:00.045 --> 00:12:02.199
And  you discover many things

00:12:02.399 --> 00:12:09.414
Like I remember, when I was in college I didn't know about google summer of code and all that 

00:12:09.614 --> 00:12:13.757
I got to know about it when the one besides me was checking the page 

00:12:13.758 --> 00:12:15.424
I asked him then he told 

00:12:15.624 --> 00:12:19.385
Then I got tot know that some one got in google summer of code and they are getting 3 lakhs in a month

00:12:19.585 --> 00:12:22.100
At that time 3 lakhs was very much 

00:12:22.300 --> 00:12:27.630
Then I tried for google summer of code 

00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:30.228
All these things happens organically by itself 

00:12:30.428 --> 00:12:32.649
Because you are with people who are with you 

00:12:32.849 --> 00:12:35.364
That defines tier 1 

00:12:35.564 --> 00:12:36.990
What happens in tier 3?

00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:39.257
I would like to explain it with another example 

00:12:39.258 --> 00:12:43.660
In Lucknow there was a friend of mine who had joined a college there 

00:12:43.860 --> 00:12:49.201
And there the situation is like, if he wants to read then other people abuse him 

00:12:49.401 --> 00:12:54.058
There tradition is like sit at one place and chill 

00:12:54.258 --> 00:12:56.252
So this is the norm 

00:12:56.452 --> 00:12:59.763
Some one is working hard that is exception 

00:12:59.963 --> 00:13:04.297
So for this reason it is very hard to give effort on this for one or two persons also 

00:13:04.497 --> 00:13:06.218
As there is no motivation at all from the surrounding 

00:13:06.418 --> 00:13:08.671
In fact people are trying to pull you down 

00:13:08.672 --> 00:13:11.181
So this difference comes because of that reason 

00:13:11.381 --> 00:13:13.662
What type of people are around you

00:13:13.862 --> 00:13:20.311
Unfortunate is that education level is little broken 

00:13:20.511 --> 00:13:23.664
It should be fixed , but at present tier 1 or 3 is defined by that

00:13:23.864 --> 00:13:30.276
If you create people like you around you , make 5 people group 

00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:35.380
And they should be serious about studies , motivate each other 

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:40.866
They fight, then you are already in a tier 1

00:13:41.066 --> 00:13:45.043
Because it is not like that if you are a tier 3 , then company will not take you 

00:13:45.243 --> 00:13:49.888
They will ask same question from everyone 

00:13:50.088 --> 00:13:55.466
Who ever answers will be taken , simple logic , no one will say that he/she is from NSIT take  him

00:13:55.666 --> 00:13:58.725
Question will be asked if you answer then you will be taken 

00:13:58.925 --> 00:14:04.487
Mentality , if there is crowd then I will also do it with crowd 

00:14:04.687 --> 00:14:06.862
I will also do it

00:14:07.062 --> 00:14:11.873
Leg pulling is everywhere , we can't do anything about it

00:14:12.073 --> 00:14:15.994
I think communities will grow , as awareness will increase 

00:14:16.194 --> 00:14:22.423
2 years ago there were coding channels in single digits on youtube 

00:14:22.623 --> 00:14:27.638
If I had to understand something then at that time there was no youtuber like that 

00:14:27.838 --> 00:14:36.537
At present everything is available , off campus opportunities 

00:14:36.737 --> 00:14:39.200
Tier -3 has got the awareness 

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:42.869
It will grow with time 

00:14:43.069 --> 00:14:49.924
If I talk about the college , where the education system is lagging 

00:14:50.124 --> 00:14:52.936
Many things are broken 

00:14:53.136 --> 00:14:56.925
Like , one more example from Lucknow , from where I belong

00:14:57.125 --> 00:15:00.078
There is a college , I can't take the name 

00:15:00.278 --> 00:15:08.447
There is a tradition that students that are not placed , are hired as teachers in that college 

00:15:08.647 --> 00:15:14.349
If these type of teachers are being hired , then I don't know what type of teaching is happening there 

00:15:14.549 --> 00:15:21.347
There are useless colleges where anyone is hired as a teachers 

00:15:21.547 --> 00:15:28.464
The colleges which are little good , there teachers are not hired because of there teaching , but because of there researching

00:15:28.664 --> 00:15:32.361
Both are not interconnected 

00:15:32.561 --> 00:15:38.105
My ability to teach is not proportional to my ability to research 

00:15:38.305 --> 00:15:42.377
My knowledge level is not indicative of how good I teach 

00:15:42.577 --> 00:15:49.443
So this is broken , in fact I believe that whose who are teaching should be practitioner

00:15:49.643 --> 00:15:53.246
They build software, that's why they are teaching

00:15:53.446 --> 00:15:56.812
Not the theory 

00:15:57.012 --> 00:16:00.216
If I take more examples , the basic subjects 

00:16:00.416 --> 00:16:05.751
OS, networks , data bases , are taught in theoretical way 

00:16:05.951 --> 00:16:12.641
If you see carefully , that students don't have love for there teachers 

00:16:12.841 --> 00:16:18.805
They are understanding things from youtuber bhaiya 

00:16:19.005 --> 00:16:23.470
This is actually useful , I will tell this to interviewer , this person is my friend 

00:16:23.670 --> 00:16:24.544
Not the teacher 

00:16:24.744 --> 00:16:28.536
He is teaching me analog , digital , or the DSA 

00:16:28.736 --> 00:16:30.333
This is not of that level 

00:16:30.533 --> 00:16:36.438
If I tell you by my experience , in our case not all the teachers but there were 2-3 teachers 

00:16:36.638 --> 00:16:40.997
They used to see NPTL lectures before coming to class , made the notes 

00:16:41.197 --> 00:16:42.436
Then used to teach us 

00:16:42.636 --> 00:16:46.569
So in this way you can't make the student strong 

00:16:46.769 --> 00:16:48.861
You can't provide them all the skills 

00:16:49.061 --> 00:16:50.567
You yourself has studied it half an hour ago , you don't have  the depth knowledge

00:16:50.767 --> 00:16:52.785
I am not saying teacher is useless 

00:16:52.985 --> 00:16:55.824
But I want to say don't do it like that

00:16:56.024 --> 00:17:00.645
An individual already working in Microsoft , Amazon 

00:17:00.845 --> 00:17:04.868
He/she can tell you more accurately , 

00:17:05.068 --> 00:17:09.225
Follow these practices ., you should know these questions 

00:17:09.425 --> 00:17:14.425
Then you can crack the interview , same person is working there and also taking the interview 

00:17:14.625 --> 00:17:16.925
That person is practitioner

00:17:17.125 --> 00:17:20.146
He has already done it, it is easy for him 

00:17:20.346 --> 00:17:25.398
But who has became teacher on the basis of research , they may have not the clarity

00:17:25.598 --> 00:17:30.678
This already happens in medical field , doctor teaches students 

00:17:30.878 --> 00:17:38.103
I know what type of cases are coming daily , I am able to utilize it

00:17:38.303 --> 00:17:41.901
This is not happening in CSE 

00:17:42.101 --> 00:17:49.424
2. Some people give argument that , some people don't want to do job 

00:17:49.624 --> 00:17:52.470
Some want to do research , I completely agree 

00:17:52.670 --> 00:17:57.323
But the research which is good is moving towards industry , industry research 

00:17:57.523 --> 00:18:02.389
The best research labs today are Google AI lab 

00:18:02.589 --> 00:18:09.331
Facebook AI lab , Amazon AI centres , these guys are doing the best edge cutting research 

00:18:09.531 --> 00:18:14.603
That are producing devices and results , that we are going on a daily basis 

00:18:14.803 --> 00:18:21.172
Today we use Alexa , I say random things in Hindi/English and it takes the action

00:18:21.372 --> 00:18:24.505
This was not imaginable 

00:18:24.705 --> 00:18:26.228
Like 10 years back 

