00:41:28.667 --> 00:41:39.914
Google has its own tech stack ,  Goldman sachs has its own Java , In Facebook there was different Php , H php

00:41:40.114 --> 00:41:51.591
If I will evaluate some at particular tech stack then it might not be productive in their case 

00:41:51.791 --> 00:41:55.027
So they evaluate on the basis of core 

00:41:55.227 --> 00:41:58.463
Why they evaluate on DSA ? there are 3-4 reasons 

00:41:58.663 --> 00:42:08.638
1. In one day the no of request are so high that the code I will write , will be executed billions times 

00:42:08.838 --> 00:42:15.526
If I have written it inefficiently , the company has to bare the cost , they need the machines , which are costly

00:42:15.726 --> 00:42:21.460
If I write useless code , then company may have to spend in millions 

00:42:21.660 --> 00:42:25.199
People should understand it

00:42:25.399 --> 00:42:31.623
Hence DSA is important , I can relate , when i say to find the optimal solution

00:42:31.823 --> 00:42:36.963
Bring O(n^2) to O( n log n) , that's why we are doing it , your no of operations will be increased 

00:42:37.163 --> 00:42:41.828
If you write in log n then it is optimal , performance will be increased 

00:42:42.028 --> 00:42:45.689
Less machines will be used , cost will be reduced 

00:42:45.889 --> 00:42:53.294
This is 1 reason , 2nd as much you practice your coding accuracy will increase 

00:42:53.494 --> 00:42:59.554
If a developer spends 1 hour to write the code , then he/she spends 10 hours to debug and test 

00:42:59.754 --> 00:43:04.799
If code accuracy is high , then time to debug and test will be reduced 

00:43:04.999 --> 00:43:08.151
Which means you become more productive 

00:43:08.351 --> 00:43:17.127
There is concept of 10X engineers , who are 10 X productive than normal engineers 

00:43:17.327 --> 00:43:21.335
If you are able to do these things , then you can become 10X productive 

00:43:21.535 --> 00:43:24.747
So these correlations are seen by companies , in there context it might make sence 

00:43:24.947 --> 00:43:27.302
It is easy to standardise interviews 

00:43:27.502 --> 00:43:29.478
Either you solved or not solved 

00:43:29.678 --> 00:43:36.263
So that's why they focus on DSA , it will not go away , it will remain the part of interview 

00:43:36.463 --> 00:43:40.294
It may happen , dev ratio increases 

00:43:40.494 --> 00:43:48.877
Coinbase ,strike has introduced a round in their interviews 

00:43:49.077 --> 00:43:54.937
Where they give you a code base , and say there is a bug , find it

00:43:55.137 --> 00:44:01.302
It doesn't matter whether you found it or not , they want to see how you are finding it

00:44:01.502 --> 00:44:04.266
What processes you are following 

00:44:04.466 --> 00:44:11.385
This may increase , but DSA will be there , as part , % may decrease 

00:44:11.585 --> 00:44:20.216
There is one more thing , If I am interviewing as SDE 1 , no one is asking design pattern 

00:44:20.416 --> 00:44:25.657
What is single tone , it can be asked 

00:44:25.857 --> 00:44:31.117
Flipkart has a round machine coding round , it is designed very well 

00:44:31.317 --> 00:44:33.775
I gave it , it is very good 

00:44:33.975 --> 00:44:38.117
You may not solve the question , but you will enjoy the round 

00:44:38.317 --> 00:44:46.900
You have been given the problem statement , requirements , now think how to use data base , which data structure I will use 

00:44:47.100 --> 00:44:50.218
How will I design 

00:44:50.418 --> 00:44:54.323
It is fun to do , in solving DSA , it is ok that you have passed all the test cases 

00:44:54.523 --> 00:45:00.384
This design game is good , it will be included , it will come there 

00:45:00.584 --> 00:45:07.091
Low level design , specially OOPs related design will be asked from SDE 1  in near future 

00:45:07.291 --> 00:45:13.380
In majority cases , it is asked at SDE 2 level ,

00:45:13.580 --> 00:45:18.087
And basic networking question will be also included 

00:45:18.287 --> 00:45:24.363
So don't be depended on DSA , explore things , it will be beneficial for you 

00:45:24.563 --> 00:45:33.408
Yesterday I had a webinar in Thapar institute 

00:45:33.608 --> 00:45:35.850
Day before yesterday in Candigar university

00:45:36.050 --> 00:45:45.647
I saw a common doubt , there is mobile dev , web dev , IOS dev , machine learning , more things are coming 

00:45:45.847 --> 00:45:51.495
When I go to do one thing , then I see there is less scope , in web there is more scope 

00:45:51.695 --> 00:45:56.061
Then I think there is more scope in machine learning 

00:45:56.261 --> 00:45:59.887
So FOMO is created in my mind , I will be left behind , I will choose the wrong one 

00:46:00.087 --> 00:46:05.005
When i have so many choices , Then How I will deal it

00:46:05.205 --> 00:46:09.613
It may happen that what I choose , it has no scope 

00:46:09.813 --> 00:46:12.636
Then what to do , 

00:46:12.836 --> 00:46:17.537
I will take 2-3 examples , people may know them 

00:46:17.737 --> 00:46:23.061
With me there were two persons , who lived with me in US in facebook 

00:46:23.261 --> 00:46:28.816
One of them is a machine learning engineer in insta , it works in news feed team 

00:46:29.016 --> 00:46:34.622
The other person is the VR engineer , metaverse engineer for Oculus

00:46:34.822 --> 00:46:38.532
Both background is that both know coding very well , they knew the coding

00:46:38.732 --> 00:46:42.339
Design concepts , which is the base 

00:46:42.539 --> 00:46:47.251
You have created a very solid base  , upon which you can create any building 

00:46:47.451 --> 00:46:56.084
Then he learned machine learning , and also learned VR, And learned   quickly 

00:46:56.284 --> 00:47:03.863
In fact now , everyone knows Tanay Pratab , he is building a metaverse 

00:47:04.063 --> 00:47:10.892
He doesn't have any background in metaverse , his base is solid , upon which you can create any building 

00:47:11.092 --> 00:47:18.611
The most important thing to understand is , base should be solid 

00:47:18.811 --> 00:47:25.907
1st create the solid fundamentals , you should know coding very well , problem solving should be good 

00:47:26.107 --> 00:47:30.122
LLD concepts should be good , little dev 

00:47:30.322 --> 00:47:37.401
Then technology will come , you can learn them , you can learn metaverse 

00:47:37.601 --> 00:47:39.274
Block chain 

00:47:39.474 --> 00:47:45.174
Web 3, web dev , with time you can learn all these things 

00:47:45.374 --> 00:47:53.875
But if base is not solid , then whatever you learn will be waste 

00:47:54.075 --> 00:48:00.100
When I started to do dev in college time 

00:48:00.300 --> 00:48:06.626
Machine learning was looking hard, I either do android or web 

00:48:06.826 --> 00:48:12.265
I took courses from Udemy , and started , after 15 days , I was not enjoying it

00:48:12.465 --> 00:48:18.993
Then started android , it was looking good 

00:48:19.193 --> 00:48:27.396
Then I continued ,my advise is if you have 5 things , then try them all 

00:48:27.596 --> 00:48:36.118
You may not get the entire picture , but you will get the general idea 

00:48:36.318 --> 00:48:38.594
Then continue 

00:48:38.794 --> 00:48:43.327
this can be one strategy , you can follow it

00:48:43.527 --> 00:48:48.477
Your base should be strong , if base is not strong , then you will be not able to do it

00:48:48.677 --> 00:48:51.096
You will only waste time 

00:48:51.296 --> 00:48:53.669
You should keep it in mind 

00:48:53.869 --> 00:48:59.988
1 very important question to you , if you are 21 years old now 

00:49:00.188 --> 00:49:07.720
Then what points you will tell yourself not to do , or things to keep in mind 

00:49:07.920 --> 00:49:16.783
Which will be beneficial to you , and the audience 

00:49:16.983 --> 00:49:21.174
3 things , that you will tell 

00:49:21.374 --> 00:49:27.883
It is interesting question , one two things I have done correct and I am thankful to that 

00:49:28.083 --> 00:49:32.868
I focused on building basics in college

00:49:33.068 --> 00:49:38.730
When I started working then realised some mistakes that I made 

00:49:38.930 --> 00:49:47.413
Every developer does it, people think that task has been given , written the code , task has been done 

00:49:47.613 --> 00:49:53.975
Actually , any developer job is not done after writing the code , then how many people are using it

00:49:54.175 --> 00:50:00.461
Is there any problem coming , then job ends 

00:50:00.661 --> 00:50:04.067
The optimization that you did is it working or not

00:50:04.267 --> 00:50:09.845
Overall you created the graph , how much time it is taking , it is dipping or not 

00:50:10.045 --> 00:50:13.428
From that it is decided that your work has been done or not 

00:50:13.628 --> 00:50:22.632
I was the task solver , later on became a engineer looking on the entire picture 

00:50:22.832 --> 00:50:30.208
2. In starting soft skills were very bad ,

00:50:30.408 --> 00:50:34.878
Plus when you move to US , there is a kind of fear , how will I talk to any one 

00:50:35.078 --> 00:50:44.971
When any one will talk about soft skills , I used to think that it is Gyaan , why to listen it

00:50:45.171 --> 00:50:50.539
Over period of time realised that , it is very important skill , because when you will do something 

00:50:50.739 --> 00:50:53.615
You will not do it alone , you will do it in a team 

00:50:53.815 --> 00:51:00.087
You have to take everyone together , you have to take suggestions from everyone 

00:51:00.287 --> 00:51:05.511
We call it stack holder management , everyone's growth is important

00:51:05.711 --> 00:51:10.235
I realised it later 

00:51:10.435 --> 00:51:17.801
It is important , if I have to go back then I will focus on it right from day one

00:51:18.001 --> 00:51:24.379
3. related to startup , the one mistake that I made 

00:51:24.579 --> 00:51:32.370
After Facebook I directly started startup , Facebook ,Google ,Amazon are different kind of world 

00:51:32.570 --> 00:51:43.765
Here you write the code , but what is going on in marketing , sales , what type of strategy goes in content , there is no exposure

00:51:43.965 --> 00:51:50.990
So I learned it all by doing mistakes , it took time 

00:51:51.190 --> 00:52:02.068
If i went back , I will 1st join a early  stage company , where I try to understand all these things by working 1 year 

00:52:02.268 --> 00:52:06.608
How it works , what mistakes they made , what is the right structure to run 

00:52:06.808 --> 00:52:09.531
Then I would have started 

00:52:09.731 --> 00:52:16.558
3rd point is mind opening , I didn't think on this by this perspective , it is logical 

00:52:16.758 --> 00:52:24.538
You go with the mind set that you will work in the company , collect the capital , knowledge 

00:52:24.738 --> 00:52:28.666
then start the startup 

00:52:28.866 --> 00:52:35.496
In starting of interview bit you didn't know sales , marketing 

00:52:35.696 --> 00:52:42.411
But if we had applied this strategy there , then there we have been able to see how things are building from scratch

00:52:42.611 --> 00:52:47.318
then we would have started interview bit , then we would have grown more 

00:52:47.518 --> 00:52:52.754
This is good point , I can think of applying it`

00:52:52.954 --> 00:52:55.931
This is logical 

00:52:56.131 --> 00:52:58.932
Would you like to give some advise to audience, one thing that we should keep in mind 

00:52:59.132 --> 00:53:04.306
Whether you are doing startup or coding , or anything else 

00:53:04.506 --> 00:53:07.608
Then we will end this session 

00:53:07.808 --> 00:53:15.841
I have one advise that , people don't discuss about there dreams with each other 

00:53:16.041 --> 00:53:19.836
Our 1st class in scaler is dare to dream 

00:53:20.036 --> 00:53:26.595
Every journeys starting point is that you dreamed 

00:53:26.795 --> 00:53:29.537
Then you start  to fight 

00:53:29.737 --> 00:53:38.547
My advise to everybody is that dare to dream , dream about what you can do in life , and then go and achieve it

00:53:38.747 --> 00:53:42.220
But start with dream, it is ok to dare to dream 

00:53:42.420 --> 00:53:46.453
Yes sir if we don't know where to go , then we would be not able to run in that direction 

00:53:46.653 --> 00:53:54.415
1st decide the path , then start running to it, introspect in intervals that you are going in correct direction or not by some experienced person 

00:53:54.615 --> 00:53:59.700
You should know the direction , where to go 

00:53:59.900 --> 00:54:04.073
Thanks sir, it was fun in this session 

00:54:04.273 --> 00:54:09.273
that's it for this video, we will meet in the next video, Bye Bye!!

